Positive numeric values with unit string suffixes. No signs or exponentials accepted. Must have at least one digit before and after the first unit string suffix. The fraction part is limited to two digits and is assumed to be in hundredths. Numeric values may be represented by halfwidth or fullwidth forms. Unit string suffix is required after the integer part but optional after the fraction part (e.g., '３，０００円５銭', '3.000 euro 5 cent').
